 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/28/02 12:13:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2204.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Evils trading with Goods hypocritical?</span><hr size=1> Eliezer that's not my point, but to answer your question:<br>
<br>
There are a lot of things my character does that I don't roleplay through or are done in an 'abbreviated' from do to game mechanics.<br>
<br>
If someone where to ask me IC if I had a weapon to sell and I happened to be carrying a dark weaver, I would show it to them in a trade window. The other player could then look at it, then deside if its something that his character would like. We could do this and stay completely IC.<br>
<br>
But if I go to the Bazaar and /auc or use the market channel, then that is OOC. What my character is doing is setting up a stall so passerby's can see my wares. Currently the game mechanics don't support PC venders, so this is used to accomplish that effect. If I /auc a dark weaver with its stats thats OOC. IC the buyer came to my stall, saw the weapon, tested it out (to see if its well balanced and if he felt he knew how to use it).<br>
<br>
It would be great if EQ supported IC shopping but it doesn't. The game engine is about killing things not shopping, There are a lot of things about your character that you never see,  do to limitations of the engine. There is a house in her hometown where she grew up and her parents live.When travelling to her hometown she would probably stop there and say hello, perhaps get a home cooked meal. Her guild would have a meeting hall were they all got together and discussed the stuff  you're hearing in /GUILD now. Etc... All this stuff would exist if you wrote a story about your character and wanted to flesh it out to give her character, but you'll never see it in game.<br>
